<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p>
Use the automatizer to auto-inscribe and autopickup your scolls of identify with @r4 
</p>
<p>
Make a macro that does r4 when you press F4 
</p>
<p>
Use the automatizer to auto-inscribe your scolls of *identify* with @r9 
</p>
<p>
Make a macro that does r9 when you press shift-F4 
</p>
<p>
The 'r' means the macro it will affect only reading. You can have other @4 items for other actions than reading. 
</p>
<h2 id="head-14c4b3886cc7a8561628f3f70e43212678e6d5b4">temporary chatter</h2>
<p>
Some players have claimed to make a macro that tries for a rod of ID, and only if it fails(lack of mana) it will read a scroll of ID instead. I couldn't duplicate this trick cleanly yet, I've still got somewhat irritating auto-inscribe messages that are annoying. Check it out in advanced techniques. 
</p>
